# Project Context

This project is the **Starfield Starmap Explorer** — a single-file, browser-based interactive galaxy map for the game *Starfield* by Bethesda.

It is a **personal offline tool** — no server, no accounts, no syncing. Progress and notes are saved locally via `localStorage`, `IndexedDB`, and the File System Access API (for folder-based JSON saves).

The entire application lives in one file: `Starmap_-_Fav_v3_.html` (or the current version).
There are no build tools, no framework, no npm.

## Aspiration / Reference

The design aspiration is the feature set found at **mapgenie.io/starfield** — specifically:
- Category/type filter sidebar (toggleable icon groups)
- Quick search by system name
- Progress tracker (mark systems as explored / scanned)
- Notes per map point
- Clean legend and category grouping
- Smooth pan and zoom

The implementation stays **offline-only** — no external API calls, no sync.

## Tech Stack

- **Single `.html` file** — all CSS and JS inline
- **Tailwind CSS** via CDN (`https://cdn.tailwindcss.com`) — utility classes used throughout
- **Font Awesome 6** via CDN — icon set for map points and UI
- **Modern JavaScript (ES6+)** — `const`, `let`, arrow functions, `async/await`, template literals are all in use. Do NOT convert to ES5/`var`.
- No npm, no bundler, no imports/exports
- Runs directly from `file://` in any modern browser (Chrome recommended for File System Access API)

## Core Data Model

### `starSystemsData[]`
Array of star system objects. Shape:
```js
{
  id: 'sol',            // unique string key
  name: 'Sol',          // display name
  x: 1234,              // pixel x on the starmap canvas
  y: 567,               // pixel y on the starmap canvas
  level: 1,             // difficulty tier (1–4, maps to point1–point4 CSS class)
  type: 'main',         // category string (e.g. 'main', 'faction', 'poi', etc.)
  description: '...'    // optional flavour text shown in the info panel
}
```

### `systemStates{}`
Object keyed by system `id`. Shape:
```js
{
  'sol': {
    explored: true,     // boolean — player has visited
    scanned: false,     // boolean — player has scanned
    note: 'My note'     // string — free-text note
  }
}
```

## Save System

Three save paths exist:
1. **localStorage** (`starfieldStarmapStates`) — auto-saved on every state change. Primary save.
2. **IndexedDB** (`starmapSaveFolder`) — persists a `FileSystemDirectoryHandle` across sessions.
3. **File System Access API** — saves/loads named `.json` files to/from a user-chosen folder.

### Rules
- `saveSystemStates()` must be called after every mutation to `systemStates`.
- `loadSystemStates()` reads from localStorage on boot.
- `applyLoadedSaveData(data)` merges loaded JSON into `systemStates` and calls `saveSystemStates()`.

## What the App Does (current v3)

- Pan and zoom the galaxy map (drag + scroll wheel)
- Click a map point to open an info panel (name, description, explored/scanned status, note icon)
- Mark systems as explored (left-click the system label)
- Mark systems as scanned (click the scan icon on the map point)
- Add/edit free-text notes per system (click the note icon)
- Progress counter: total systems / explored / scanned
- Reset all exploration
- Save progress to a folder as a named `.json` file
- Load progress from a saved `.json` file

## Working Rules

- Do not remove existing working features unless explicitly asked.
- Preserve existing UI patterns and interaction behaviour unless the task changes them.
- Prefer small, targeted changes over full rewrites.
- After editing, verify that save/load, pan/zoom, and the note modal all still work.
- Never introduce server-side calls, authentication, or sync features — this remains offline.
- Keep CDN links to Tailwind and Font Awesome as-is unless explicitly asked to remove them.
- Do not introduce additional CDN dependencies without asking first.

